{
  "texts": [
    "The xAPI enables the tracking of learner activity and performance data across many platforms and systems, which is intended to address some of the drawbacks of LMSs.",
    "With the help of the xAPI, a variety of learning activities (including taking quizzes, viewing videos, and engaging in discussion forums) can be recorded and analyzed.",
    "Therefore, xAPI has been used by Akour et al (2020); Liu et al (2022b) for a deeper knowledge of learner performance and engagement.",
    "• The ASSISTments dataset is a publicly accessible dataset that contains data on student engagement and performance in online mathematics and science courses collected between 2004 and 2013 by the Worcester Polytechnic Institute and Carnegie Mellon University.",
    "The dataset contains a wide range of student's features, including demographics, engagement, and academic achievement."
  ]
}